properties.Title: Bernie 2020 Community Canvass in Montgomery County, PA
properties.Address:
South Wood Street & West Main Street
Lansdale, PA 19446
properties.Description: Come together with family, friends and neighbors to talk to voters in your community about the election. We'll be asking folks to share what issues are important to them this election, and telling our stories of why we're supporting Bernie in 2020. Using the BERN app, we will do the critical work of helping the campaign identify who is likely to support Bernie.

properties.Title: ARTS DISTRICT FOR BERNIE! Bernie 2020 Phonebank in Arts District / Downtown LA
properties.Description:
Join us for Bernie in the Arts District, right next to Little Tokyo! Come together with friends, family, and neighbors to call voters in support of Bernie!

Phonebanking is one of the most important things you can do to help our campaign win. Every call helps us grow our movement, turn Bernie supporters out to vote, and win this election in a landslide.

Note: In addition to a cell phone, please bring a laptop or tablet to use to make calls on the Bernie Dialer.

Call when you're here: 617.519.3891 OR use the intercom and search for "double J".

Street parking is available.

We're also easily accessible using the below public transportation options:

•     Via bus on the DASH A stop at Traction Ave & Merrick. This stop is directly across the street from the phone bank!

•     Via the Gold Line, we're an 8-10 minute walk from the Arts District / Little Tokyo stop.

**Note:** In addition to a cell phone, please bring a laptop or tablet (laptop is better) to use to make calls on the Bernie Dialer. Headphones that plug into your phone are also helpful.

We will be knocking on doors and speaking directly to voters about Bernie Sanders and his vision for our country.

Talking to voters face-to-face is the best way to get them out to the polls.

If you’ve never canvassed before, don’t worry! We’ll give you a quick training before you head out to make sure you feel confident as you go out to meet voters around town!

Wear weather-appropriate clothing, comfortable shoes, and bring water, and a charged cell phone.

properties.Title: Bernie 2020 Table at Davis Farmers Market Community Canvass
properties.Description:
Come join us at the Bernie 2020 table at the Davis Farmers Market in Downtown Davis. We will be talking to voters at the market about the primary election and Bernie 2020's transformative platform. You do not have to attend the entire time but we will be tabling from 9:00 am to 1:00 pm. You can drop by anytime you like and leave when you like.

We are building a local Davis for Bernie group with room for Bernie 2020 supporters like you to join us so we can start doing more voter outreach and registration for Bernie 2020 in Davis. This will be a fun and low-stress event. We will be asking people to share what issues are important to them this election and sharing our stories of why we're supporting Bernie. We will be using the BERN app to gauge people's interest in the campaign.

You don’t have to come for the whole time. Even one hour is fine!

Come to my Plan to Win party to hear what it’s going to take to win the primaries and complete the political revolution.

properties.Title: Bernie 2020 Table at Davis Farmers Market Community Canvass
properties.Description:
Come join us at the Bernie 2020 table at the Davis Farmers Market in Downtown Davis. We will be talking to voters at the market about the primary election and Bernie 2020's transformative platform. You do not have to attend the entire time but we will be tabling from 9:00 am to 1:00 pm. You can drop by anytime you like and leave when you like.

We are building a local Davis for Bernie group with room for Bernie 2020 supporters like you to join us so we can start doing more voter outreach and registration for Bernie 2020 in Davis. This will be a fun and low-stress event. We will be asking people to share what issues are important to them this election and sharing our stories of why we're supporting Bernie. We will be using the BERN app to gauge people's interest in the campaign.

You don’t have to come for the whole time. Even one hour is fine!

You do not have to attend the entire time but we will be tabling from 9:30 am to 1:00 pm. You can drop by anytime you like and leave when you like.

We are building a local Davis for Bernie group with room for Bernie 2020 supporters like you to join us so we can start doing more voter outreach and registration for Bernie 2020 in Davis. This will be a fun and low-stress event. We will be asking people to share what issues are important to them this election and sharing our stories of why we're supporting Bernie. We will be using the BERN app to gauge people's interest in the campaign.

You don’t have to come for the whole time. Even one hour is fine!

properties.Title: December Debate Watch Party in Oceanside, CA
properties.Description:
Come join us for the Sixth Democratic Debate featuring fewer candidates! At this time, there are six qualifying candidates for the December Debate. The live debate begins at 5:00, but we're hoping you'll be able to join in our Debate Watch Party as early as 4:00. Of course, arriving whenever you can works well, too! As an aside, a little bird told me there would not be a Debate Watch Party in Encinitas in December. We hope all will join in here.

We'll have Happy Hour from 3:00 to 6:00, so we'll have plenty of time to enjoy the special prices on appetizers and drinks. The prices at 19TEN Oceanside are reasonable in any case, so we're good no matter what time you arrive. Of course, purchases are optional.

We'll have all the televisions and the big screen tuned in to the debate. The excellent integrated sound system will be tuned in, as well. You'll be able to hear and see from wherever you are seated, and we'll have closed captioning on the televisions and the big screen, too!

On the Sprinter, exit at the Crouch Street Station. Walk southwest, 725 feet, and cross Oceanside Boulevard. If driving, from the 5 freeway, take exit 52, Oceanside Boulevard. Go east on Oceanside Boulevard, about a half-mile. Turn left into the strip mall, before Taco Bell and just before the Black Rock Coffee Bar kiosk. 19TEN Oceanside has a sign that says Sports Bar and it's deep into the parking lot. We're ADA accessible, with closed captioning on all the televisions. Because 19TEN is a pub, attendees must be 21 and up.

Come together with your friends, family members, and neighbors for this fun event and cheer for Bernie at the 6th 2020 Presidential Democratic Primary Debate! Get excited about our historic campaign to transform America, and sign up to do the important work of grassroots organizing.

Of course, we welcome all interested viewers. Thank you, everybody, for coming out to participate in democracy.

properties.Title: Bernie 2020 Phonebank in Escondido, CA
properties.Description:
The Official Bernie Campaign is here in North San Diego!!

The CA ‪March 3rd‬ Primary is coming up quick. CA has the most delegates of any state. If you come out to knock and call, we'll win CA, we'll win the Nomination, we'll bring power back to the People in the White House and we'll start fundamentally changing America to work for all of us.
Some of us will be doing Volunteer 2 Volunteer Calls, which are the most powerful calls. All we do is call fellow Bernie Volunteers to plug them into Canvasses, Phone Banks, and other Bernie Events in our area. For every Volunteer you get signed up to Knock or Call, that will become 100s or 1,000s of knocks and calls by the time of the CA Primary ‪on March 3rd.‬ Join the Vol 2 Vol Call Team and let's grow our Bernie community in CD 50!
The rest of us will be using the Bernie Dialer to reach out to Voters to share our stories and get those Votes to WIN! #NotMeUs
PHONE BANKERS: Bring a laptop or tablet (an extra if you have one in case someone needs one), cell phone, phone charger, reusable water bottle, and headphones if you have them. If you can't arrive by ‪5:00 p.m.‬, come when you can. We'll get you set up and started whenever you arrive.

Come together with friends, family, neighbors, the whole local Bernie Community! Phonebanking is one of the most important things you can do. Every call helps us grow our Movement, to turn Bernie supporters out to vote, and to win this election in a People's landslide.
Note: In addition to a cell phone and charger, please bring a laptop or tablet to make Bernie calls, reusable water bottle, and headphones if you have them! #InBernieWeTrust

properties.Title: Bernie 2020 Community Canvass in Ocala, FL
properties.Description:
The BERNIE SANDERS 2020 CAMPAIGN has come to town!

We opened our Bernie Sanders Volunteer Campaign Ocala Headquarters at 4315 Se 10th Place Ocala, Florida 34471 on Wednesday, May 15, 2019, so folks could greet and meet and plan future community events to conduct and participate within our area over the next year's 2020 campaign. We have been busy since then.

We are a growing group of Marion County citizens and voters, running the full spectrum of age and backgrounds who are active in our communities to dump Trump and support Bernie Sanders for President; find and support our local, state and federal progressive candidates campaigning to be elected to our public offices; and to place the following progressive initiatives on the 2020 election ballot.

PROVIDE MEDICARE FOR ELIGIBLE LOW-INCOME ADULTS [Ballot Initiative Serial # 18-16]

RAISING FLORIDA’S MINIMUM WAGE ($15 LIVABLE WAGE) [Ballot Initiative Serial # 18-01]

PROHIBITS POSSESSION OF DEFINED ASSAULT WEAPONS [ Ballot Initiative Serial # 19-01]

RIGHT OF ADULTS TO CANNABIS [Ballot Initiative Serial # 15-20]

These petitions are one of the most effective ways to walk up and interact with local voters “cold” and many participate since the issues and proposed laws are popular with voters to sign.

Quite a few voters become new volunteers in our statewide campaign to create positive changes here at home and around Florida.

Local and Florida State candidates who support our popular progressive petitions appreciate the support we can offer in turn, using our petitions as "links" between voters and progressive candidates in a necessary “double round” of elections in 2020 & 2022 to create change.

A new state law, HB-5, was made effective just after our last 4th of July Independence Day holiday that eviscerates the right of Florida citizens to sign ballot initiative petitions, like these listed here, in order to vote in the next election to approve them. Several of the most popular, beneficial petition drives were ended due to the changes made by Florida politicians to end our right to petition to vote.

This HB-5 law was passed now to stop these petitions and to discourage progressive voters from coming to vote in 2020. This suppression of the vote will be challenged in federal court by a group, FL CITIZENS RIGHT TO PETITION, which includes several of our Bernie volunteers, here in Marion County, Florida.

We seek Bernie campaign volunteers, neighborhood canvassers, interested voters and those willing to assist by collecting Florida voter signed "citizen sponsored" ballot initiative petitions to place these non-partisan progressive issues on the 2020 election ballot. We accept the fact and responsibility of winning this election or not and intend to do all we can to make sure we are successful.

We meet occasionally on a weekly basis in our volunteer member’s homes, local restaurants, and other locales.

Our monthly meetings are held on the third Sunday of every month, between 1:30 PM and 3:30 PM in Room “B” of the main Marion County Library, located at 2720 E Silver Springs Blvd, Ocala, FL 34470. Signs in the library lobby will show you the way to where we are meeting. Our next scheduled meeting is Sunday, December 15th, 2019 at 1:30 PM.

Our permanent “Bernie Sanders Volunteer Office” is located at 4315 SE 10th PLACE OCALA, FL. 34471. We are in a quiet SE residential neighborhood, not far from the intersection of Silver Springs Blvd. (State Road 40 East) & NE 36 Avenue.

Please call first, to ensure we are present and available Monday - Saturday unless attending a pre-scheduled appointment, meeting or event. We are Closed on Sundays unless a special meeting is scheduled. Thank You!

Please feel free to contact and join us on Facebook, or by our phone or email.

properties.Title: Board the Bernie Bus and Knock Doors in the NH Primary!
properties.Venue: Dog River Park and Ride Montpelier
properties.Description:
There are less than 100 days before New Hampshire primary! We need to have as many face to face conversations with potential supporters as possible - that's how we'll win the Granite State and build the political revolution through February and beyond! For Vermonters, this is one of the biggest and most impactful ways to help Bernie become the next president of the United States!

If you’ve never canvassed before, don’t worry! We’ll give you a quick training on the bus for your Bernie journey. We’ll make sure you get to where you’re canvassing for our first shift so you can pound pavement for the day and hop on the Bernie Bus home in the evening! Meet other supporters from your state and team up with us in New Hampshire to win the primary in February!

properties.Title: Bernie 2020 Plan to Win Party in Madison, WI!
properties.Venue: Friends Book Store (@FmplShop), 201 W Mifflin St
properties.Description:
Come together with your friends, family, and neighbors to join our historic campaign to defeat Trump and transform America.

Bernie understands that when you stand up and fight for working people, when you do not cower to Wall Street and the mega-corporations and billionaires who rigged our economy and our democratic system, when you do this for your whole life, you give people real motivation to vote.

Bernie has given us hope. He has changed the narrative and the sense of what is possible in the entire country. He has spent his life on picket lines and in the halls of Congress fighting for working-class people.

Now it’s up to all of us to get him into the White House.

Come to my Plan to Win party to hear what it’s going to take to win the primaries and complete the political revolution.

Talking to voters face-to-face is the best way to get them out to the polls. Come meet up with our volunteer team and we’ll go knock on doors in Plaistow to round up votes for Bernie Sanders!

If you’ve never canvassed before, don’t worry! We’ll give you a quick training before you head out. We’ll have 3 different shifts every Saturday: 10 am, 1 pm and 4 pm with a quick 30 minute training before the start of each to make sure you feel confident as you go out to meet voters around town!

Just make sure to bring your smartphone, and a water bottle.

RSVP below if you’ll be there!

properties.Title: Board the Bernie Bus and Knock Doors for the NH Primary!
properties.Description:
There are less than 100 days before New Hampshire primary! We need to have as many face to face conversations with potential supporters as possible - that's how we'll win the Granite State and build the political revolution through February and beyond! For Vermonters, this is one of the biggest and most impactful ways to help Bernie become the next president of the United States!

If you’ve never canvassed before, don’t worry! We’ll give you a quick training on the bus for your Bernie journey. We’ll make sure you get to where you’re canvassing for our first shift so you can pound pavement for the day and hop on the Bernie Bus home in the evening! Meet other supporters from your state and team up with us in New Hampshire to win the primary in February!

properties.Title: Bernie Beach Center Weekly Wednesday Phonebank in Santa Monica, CA
properties.Description:
Join us for our weekly Wednesday Phonebanking Party at The Bernie Beach Center!

Come meet some new volunteer pals and get started on the phone lines. Training will be provided. Please feel free to join whenever you are free from the hours of 5:00 pm until 8 pm (when the phone lines close).

The Bernie Beach Center is a volunteer-run community space created to serve our Santa Monica and West LA neighbors. We have an entire office to ourselves with plenty of desks, chairs, smaller offices, and room for an army of phonebankers! Snacks and water will be provided.

properties.Title: Tuesday Evening Phonebanking in South Carlsbad for Bernie 2020!
properties.Venue: This event’s address is private. Sign up for more details
properties.Address:
This event’s address is private. Sign up for more details
Carlsbad, CA 92009
properties.Description:
We are only a very few months from the March 2020 CA Primary!

The Official Bernie Campaign is expanding with new Staff to North San Diego and this is our new Congressional District 49 Phone Bank!

There are two options when you join us. Volunteer to Volunteer Call Team phone bank is the first option.

Vol 2 Vol calls are the easiest and most powerful calls you can make. All we're doing is calling fellow Bernie Volunteers to plug them into Canvasses, Phone Banks, and other Bernie Events in our area. Every Volunteer you sign up to Knock or Call, that will become 100s or 1,000s of knocks and calls by the time the newly influential, early CA Primary comes on March 3. Join the Vol 2 Vol Call Team and let's grow our Bernie community in CD 49!

The second phone bank option is the Bernie Dialer.

This is an easy script that we follow and mark the responses of the people we talk to about Bernie. If you want to tell others about why a Bernie Sanders Presidency will help you or those you care about, this is a great opportunity.

You can decide that you want to call other Volunteers (Vol 2 Vol) or that you want to call registered Democrats or No Party Preference voters (Bernie Dialer) when you get here.

PHONE BANKERS: Bring a laptop or tablet (an extra, if you have one, in case someone needs one), cell phone, phone charger, and headphones if you have them. If you can't arrive by 5:00 p.m., come when you can. All your work is valuable! We'll get you set up and started whenever you arrive.

Come together with friends, family, and neighbors to call other volunteers in support of Bernie!

Phonebanking is one of the **most important things** you can do to help our campaign win. Every call helps us grow our movement, to bring out Bernie supporters to vote, and to win this election in a landslide.

Note: In addition to a cell phone, please bring a **laptop or tablet** to use to make Volunteer to Volunteer or the Bernie Dialer calls.

Thank you for signing up! From the 5 freeway, exit Leucadia Boulevard. Go east on Leucadia Boulevard about two miles. Cross El Camino Real. Turn left at the first stoplight east of El Camino Real onto Amargosa Drive. Go up the hill, passing the park on the left. The house is on the left, on the SW corner of the cul-de-sac at Sombrosa Place and Amargosa Drive. See you Tuesday!

• Any questions or suggestions, please reach out to Arturo or Madge Torres at 760.613.7035

properties.Title: Bernie 2020 Phonebank in Escondido, CA
properties.Description:
The Official Bernie Campaign is here in North San Diego!!

The CA ‪March 3rd‬ Primary is coming up quick. CA has the most delegates of any state. If you come out to knock and call, we'll win CA, we'll win the Nomination, we'll bring power back to the People in the White House and we'll start fundamentally changing America to work for all of us.
Some of us will be doing Volunteer 2 Volunteer Calls, which are the most powerful calls. All we do is call fellow Bernie Volunteers to plug them into Canvasses, Phone Banks, and other Bernie Events in our area. For every Volunteer you get signed up to Knock or Call, that will become 100s or 1,000s of knocks and calls by the time of the CA Primary ‪on March 3rd.‬ Join the Vol 2 Vol Call Team and let's grow our Bernie community in CD 50!
The rest of us will be using the Bernie Dialer to reach out to Voters to share our stories and get those Votes to WIN! #NotMeUs
PHONE BANKERS: Bring a laptop or tablet (an extra if you have one in case someone needs one), cell phone, phone charger, reusable water bottle, and headphones if you have them. If you can't arrive by ‪5:00 p.m.‬, come when you can. We'll get you set up and started whenever you arrive.

Come together with friends, family, neighbors, the whole local Bernie Community! Phonebanking is one of the most important things you can do. Every call helps us grow our Movement, to turn Bernie supporters out to vote, and to win this election in a People's landslide.
Note: In addition to a cell phone and charger, please bring a laptop or tablet to make Bernie calls, reusable water bottle, and headphones if you have them! #InBernieWeTrust

properties.Title: Medicare For All Townhall with Michael Lighty
properties.Description:
MEDICARE FOR ALL



Medicare Care for All, we hear alot about it in the new’s but what does it actually mean and how will it work?



Join Senator Bernie Sanders Healthcare Constituency Director Michael Lighty for a presentation and Q&A on Medicare For All and Single Payer.



Michael Lighty will be able to answer questions such as: how does single payer work and what does it mean for seniors as well as those on private insurance? Will Medicare For All be like the VA? I require specific medication will I be able to get it under Medicare For All? Will wait times increase? and many other questions Please bring any questions you have about single payer health care and Mr. Michael Lighty can answer it.



Michael Lighty is considered the preeminent spokesperson and expert on Medicare for All. For over 25 years, Lighty has organized, written and spoken on the subject. He is currently a lead policy analyst for a single-payer bill, SB 562, the Healthy California Act. Lighty is the chief healthcare policy advisor for Senator Sanders of Vermont and played a central role in creating the Senator’s Medicare For All Bill in the Senate.



As with any policy matter during political campaigns, it is the job of campaigns and hopefully, movements, to educate voters on the issues. How can we expect folks to understand a healthcare system which is substantially different than our present one without some sort of education?



Format: 20 Minutes of Michael speaking on the subject and introducing himself, the rest of the time will be Q&A. He wants people to have all of their questions answered.

properties.Address:

Carlsbad, CA 92009
properties.Description:
We are only a very few months from the March 2020 CA Primary!

The Official Bernie Campaign is expanding with new Staff to North San Diego and this is our new Congressional District 49 Phone Bank!

There are two options when you join us. Volunteer to Volunteer Call Team phone bank is the first option.

Vol 2 Vol calls are the easiest and most powerful calls you can make. All we're doing is calling fellow Bernie Volunteers to plug them into Canvasses, Phone Banks, and other Bernie Events in our area. Every Volunteer you sign up to Knock or Call, that will become 100s or 1,000s of knocks and calls by the time the newly influential, early CA Primary comes on March 3. Join the Vol 2 Vol Call Team and let's grow our Bernie community in CD 49!

The second phone bank option is the Bernie Dialer.

This is an easy script that we follow and mark the responses of the people we talk to about Bernie. If you want to tell others about why a Bernie Sanders Presidency will help you or those you care about, this is a great opportunity.

You can decide that you want to call other Volunteers (Vol 2 Vol) or that you want to call registered Democrats or No Party Preference voters (Bernie Dialer) when you get here.

PHONE BANKERS: Bring a laptop or tablet (an extra, if you have one, in case someone needs one), cell phone, phone charger, and headphones if you have them. If you can't arrive by 5:00 p.m., come when you can. All your work is valuable! We'll get you set up and started whenever you arrive.

Come together with friends, family, and neighbors to call other volunteers in support of Bernie!

Phonebanking is one of the most important things you can do to help our campaign win. Every call helps us grow our movement, to bring out Bernie supporters to vote, and to win this election in a landslide.

Note: In addition to a cell phone, please bring a laptop or tablet to use to make Volunteer to Volunteer or the Bernie Dialer calls.

Thank you for signing up! From the 5 freeway, exit Leucadia Boulevard. Go east on Leucadia Boulevard about two miles. Cross El Camino Real. Turn left at the first stoplight east of El Camino Real onto Amargosa Drive. Go up the hill, passing the park on the left. The house is on the left, on the SW corner of the cul-de-sac at Sombrosa Place and Amargosa Drive. See you Sunday!

• Any questions or suggestions, please reach out to Arturo or Madge Torres at 760.613.7035

Hi fellow union members! Let's bring together Bernie supporters and those Bernie curious to discuss the kind of transformation our country needs, details of Bernie's many plans, and how we can organize to inform and turn as many people as possible out to vote in the primary!
Washington state switched from a caucus system to a vote by mail primary this year, which makes convincing your friends and neighbors to vote for Bernie that much easier!
Your friends, family members, coworkers, neighbors, and classmates, are looking to you to help make their decisions about who to support for President! Studies show that relational organizing, organizing the people you know, is *the* most effective strategy for increasing turnout in an election. Bring a friend to this fun event where we make plans to organize our personal networks for Bernie using the campaign’s official BERN App. We can’t leave a single vote on the table!

Come together with friends, family, and neighbors to call voters in support of Bernie! Phonebanking is one of *the most important things* you can do to help our campaign win. Every call helps us grow our movement, turn Bernie supporters out to vote, and win this election in a landslide.

**Note:** In addition to a cell phone, please bring a laptop or tablet to use to make calls on the Bernie Dialer.

properties.Title: Official Campaign Power Canvass Hosted by Volunteer Organizer Albert in Temple City
properties.Description:
Bernie 2020 is entering the next phase of the campaign to make direct voter contact in Los Angeles County!

We are less than 71 days before 2020 primary ballots are mailed in California and every conversation matters!!!

We will be knocking on doors and speaking directly to voters about Bernie Sanders and his vision for our country.

Talking to voters face-to-face is the best way to get them out to the polls. Come meet up with our volunteer team and we’ll go knock on doors to round up votes for Bernie Sanders!

If you’ve never canvassed before, don’t worry! We’ll give you a quick training before you head out to make sure you feel confident as you go out to meet voters around town!

Bring sunscreen, a sun hat, comfy shoes, water and most importantly a friend! You can come by for a couple of hours or stay for the whole shift.

properties.Title: Bernie 2020 Community Canvass in Altadena
properties.Description: Come together with family, friends, and neighbors to talk to voters in your community about the election. We'll be asking folks to share what issues are important to them this election, and telling our stories of why we're supporting Bernie in 2020.  We will be on high visibility streets asking enthusiastic home owners if they want to display a Bernie yard sign.

properties.Address:

Portland, OR 97211
properties.Description:
Meet new friends as you make calls to help Bernie win! In this exciting 2020 race, where we are going to elect Bernie as President, the crucial early primary states vote in February which is only two months away. Additionally, California is extremely important! California has moved up their primary to Super Tuesday, March 3rd. This means we have a shorter period of time to turn undecided voters into Bernie supporters in the largest Democratic state in the country. With your help, we are going to win this!

If you are new to phone banking, no worries. People will be there to teach you how to make calls. You will need to bring a laptop or tablet as well as a cell phone. Snacks will be provided. Making these calls is fun and doing it together is a great way to meet like-minded people, so please join us!.

**Note:** In addition to a cell phone, please bring a laptop or tablet to use to make calls on the Bernie Dialer.

properties.Title: Oceanside Kickoff Bernie Canvass!  SUN 12/01, 12/08
properties.Description:
We are 2 months from Early Voting. CA has the most delegates. If we win CA, we win the Nomination, we get into the White House, and we change America for the People, for us. #NotMeUs

The Bernie Campaign is officially in North San Diego. This is our Kickoff Oceanside Canvass! Knocking doors, listening to our neighbors, and sharing why you believe in Bernie and why you believe in the power of our Movement is the only way we're going to win. Join the local Bernie Community! We'll see you Sunday by 1:30 pm!

CANVASSERS: Bring a FULLY-charged smart-phone, reusable water bottle, snack, sunscreen, comfy clothes and shoes, and have the "PDI Mobile Connect" App downloaded on your phone!

Any questions, comments, ideas, reach out to Luca Barton, Bernie 2020 Regional Field Director (North of the 8):
(213) 361-2545

properties.Title: Campaign Power Canvass Hosted by Volunteer Organizer Christopher Roman in Baldwin Park!
properties.Description:
Bernie 2020 is entering the next phase of the campaign to make direct voter contact in Los Angeles County!

Join us for our Weekend of Action . We are less than 5 months from the March 2020 primary and every conversation matters!!!

We will be knocking on doors and speaking directly to voters about Bernie Sanders and his vision for our country.

Talking to voters face-to-face is the best way to get them out to the polls. Come meet up with our volunteer team and we’ll go knock on doors to round up votes for Bernie Sanders!

If you’ve never canvassed before, don’t worry! We’ll give you a quick training before you head out to make sure you feel confident as you go out to meet voters around town!

A quick training we will be start at 11:00 am before hitting the doors. Bring sunscreen, a sun hat, comfy shoes, water and most importantly a friend! You can come by for a couple of hours or stay for the whole shift.

For information regarding logistics please contact Christopher at: chroman9393@gmail.com / 626) 201 9187

properties.Description:
Talking to voters face-to-face is the best way to get them out to the polls. Come meet up with our volunteer team and we’ll go knock on doors in Chesterfield to round up votes for Bernie Sanders!

properties.Title: #UnionMembersForBernie  Mapping Party in Corvallis, OR
properties.Description:
Hello fellow union members! Take a break from the pre-finals stress to eat some delicious food and learn how to make Bernie Sanders the 46th President of the United States! Enthusiasts and undecided voters alike are more than welcome!

Space will be limited in my little apartment but we will make it work. Please bring something to sit on ranging from collapsable chairs to pillows for the floor as seating is limited.

Also, I have a dog. (Warning to those allergic to dogs.)

\\ From the campaign:
Your friends, family members, coworkers, neighbors and classmates, are looking to you to help make their decisions about who to support for President! Studies show that relational organizing, organizing the people you know, is *the* most effective strategy for increasing turnout in an election.

Bring a friend to this fun event where we make plans to organize our personal networks for Bernie using the campaign’s official BERN App. We can’t leave a single vote on the table!

Note: Please bring a smartphone, laptop, or tablet.
\\

This is going to be a potluck so please bring a dish to share! I am also thinking about ordering some pizza. I will send you a message after you RSVP about your favorite toppings. Please inform me of any dietary restrictions.

A-J - Main Dish
K-Q - Side Dish
R-Z - Dessert (I am making vegan/gluten-free cookies!)

Super stoked to meet you all and get started!

properties.Title: Bernie 2020 Discussion with Northern Nevada Labor
properties.Description:
BERNIE 2020

International labor leader Jose La Luz will be leading a discussion with labor leaders and union workers from across Northern Nevada. La Luz will be joined by healthcare expert Michael Lighty.

After introductions, La Luz and Lighty will field questions on all topics pertinent to labor. Whether you are curious about Medicare for All or Bernie's Workplace Democracy plan, these policy experts will be able to answer those questions.

properties.Title: Campaign Power Canvass Hosted by Volunteer Organizer Michelle Boley in North Hollywood!
properties.Address:
13319 Strathern St s House
Los Angeles, CA 91605
properties.Description:
Bernie 2020 is entering the next phase of the campaign to make direct voter contact in Los Angeles County!

We are less than 5 months from the March 2020 primary and every conversation matters!!!

We will be knocking on doors in our community and speaking directly to voters about Bernie Sanders and his vision for our country.

Talking to voters face-to-face is the best way to get them out to the polls. If you’ve never canvassed before, don’t worry! We’ll give you a quick training before you head out to make sure you feel confident as you go out to meet voters around town!

Bring sunscreen, a sun hat, comfy shoes, water and most importantly a friend!

For logistical questions, please contact Michelle Boley: 310.213.8026

properties.Title: Bernie 2020 Community Canvass in Concord, CA
properties.Description:
Come join our Bay Area Bernie 2020 team to table for Bernie Sanders for President at the popular tree lighting event in downtown Concord, CA on Saturday, December 7th from 4-8 pm. You are welcome to work a two-hour shift from 4-6 pm or 6-8 pm if you want to.

Concord tree lighting will be big event . Join us in getting the word out about why Bernie is the best 2020 candidate for President, talk with our neighbors about the big issues and collect contacts of Bernie supporters so we can keep them in the loop when Bernie comes in town how and when we are organizing for Bernie 2020 here in Contra Costa County. Hope to see you there!

Todos Santos Plaza is a few blocks from Concord Bart. If you need a Bart pickup or directions please text Kate at 925-899-3309 to arrange that. There is a public parking garage kiddi corner Todos Santos Plaza if you were looking for a spot to park.

properties.Title: Bernie 2020 Phonebank in Manchester, NH
properties.Description:
In this critical first-in-the-nation NH primary election, we need as many voters as we can get to help increase turnout. Join us as we make calls and talk to our neighbors about getting out the vote in our upcoming primary! This is essential to recruiting more volunteers, rounding up lots of votes, and getting more people engaged in the political revolution!

If you’ve never phonebanked before, don’t worry! We’ll have a quick training before your first call and will be there to help if you have any questions! Also, if you can't make it right at 4pm or if you can't stay until 7pm, that's totally fine! We greatly appreciate any and all help you can offer!

properties.Title: Campaign Power Canvass Hosted by Volunteer Organizer Marta Samano in La Puente!
properties.Description:
Bernie 2020 is entering the next phase of the campaign to make direct voter contact in Los Angeles County!

Join us for our Weekend of Action . We are less than 5 months from the March 2020 primary and every conversation matters!!!

We will be knocking on doors and speaking directly to voters about Bernie Sanders and his vision for our country.

Talking to voters face-to-face is the best way to get them out to the polls. Come meet up with our volunteer team and we’ll go knock on doors to round up votes for Bernie Sanders!

If you’ve never canvassed before, don’t worry! We’ll give you a quick training before you head out to make sure you feel confident as you go out to meet voters around town!

A quick training we will be start at 11:00 am before hitting the doors. Bring sunscreen, a sun hat, comfy shoes, water and most importantly a friend! You can come by for a couple of hours or stay for the whole shift.

For information regarding logistics please contact Marta at: martasamano@gmail.com / 323) 632-4643

Come knock on doors in Westwood with volunteer organizers Max and Carley! Door knocking is a vital part of winning the CA primary for Bernie, and getting Bernie to the White House.

WHAT TO BRING

Bring sunscreen, water, comfy shoes, and a charged smartphone.

GETTING THERE

Street parking is available on Malcolm Ave. Or take the Big Blue Bus/Metro to Santa Monica and Westwood.

properties.Title: Community Canvass in Fresno
properties.Description: Join us at our new office location for a community canvass!

properties.Title: Official Power Canvass hosted by Volunteer Organizer Reggie @ Westchester Park!
properties.Venue: Westchester Park ( Bernie Table by Tennis Court Parking Lot)
properties.Description:
Bernie 2020 is entering the next phase of the campaign to make direct voter contact in LA County!

Join us for our Weekend of Action . We are less than 5 months from the March 2020 primary and every conversation matters!!!

We will be knocking on doors and speaking directly to voters about Bernie Sanders and his vision for our country.

Talking to voters face-to-face is the best way to get them out to the polls. Come meet up with our volunteer team and we’ll go knock on doors to round up votes for Bernie Sanders!

If you’ve never canvassed before, don’t worry! We’ll give you a quick training before you head out to make sure you feel confident as you go out to meet voters around town!

A quick training we will be start at 10:00 pm before hitting the doors. Bring sunscreen, a sun hat, comfy shoes, water and most importantly a friend!

properties.Title: Escondido Bernie Canvass!  SAT 11/30, 12/07, 12/14, 12/21, 12/28
properties.Description:
We are 2 months from Early Voting. CA has the most delegates. If we win CA, we win the Nomination, we get into the White House, and we change America for the People, for us. #NotMeUs

The Official Bernie Campaign is here in North San Diego. Knocking doors, listening to our neighbors, and briefly sharing why you believe in Bernie and why you believe in the power of our Movement is the only way we're going to win. Escondido is critical to winning North SD. Join us and we'll see you Sunday by 1:30 pm!

CANVASSERS: Bring a FULLY-charged smart-phone, reusable water bottle, snack, sunscreen, comfy clothes and shoes, and have the "PDI Mobile Connect" App downloaded on your phone!

Any questions, comments, ideas, reach out to Luca Barton, Bernie 2020 Regional Field Director (North of the 8):
(213) 361-2545

properties.Title: Bernie 2020 Community Canvassing  in Quincy, FL!
properties.Description:
Find us on Facebook under "Gadsden for Bernie" and come together with family, friends, and neighbors to wave signs and talk to voters in your community about the election at our second canvassing & sign-waving event! Yes, we will talk, canvass, wave signs, and educate our undecided neighbors about the wonderful things that Bernie Sanders will be bringing to the table. Let's show our community that we are ready for a political revolution.

Important instructions: We will only stand on the sidewalk that surrounds and covers all 4 sides of the courthouse. Not on the storefront sidewalks, not on the courthouse grass. Only on the sidewalks. We will begin accommodating ourselves on the front sidewalk/corners of the courthouse. Then the front, then sides, then the back if needed. All sides face traffic. Please watch your children well. Bring water and snacks for your kids if needed. There are a few benches for your convenience. There is also a Hardee's walking distance and also a very nice cafe right across the courthouse called Damfino's Cafe. They close at 2 pm on Saturdays. Safety will be your responsibility and priority!

Wear your Bernie gear, bring official Bernie signs, or make your own! You're welcome to express your creativity. If you do not have any of these, we do count with a limited number of rally signs (those need to be returned to the organizer), and stickers (for you to wear on your top and keep). Leaders of all faiths, people from all religions, atheists, teachers, refugees, immigrants, and the LGBTQ community are welcome. Everyone is welcome even if you do not reside in Gadsden County. Be ready to explain to new voters, prospective and new Berners why you are supporting Bernie!

Ideas for your own poster signs:
Legalize Marijuana Nationally
$15 an hour Bernie 2020
25% poverty level compared to a 15% poverty level, let's fix it Bernie 2020
"Housing for All" Bernie 2020
"Medicare for All" Bernie 2020
Bernie for Diversity and Inclusion
Bernie for Criminal Justice Reform
Bernie for Public Education Funds
Bernie for Teachers - 60k minimum a year
Bernie for Climate Change
Ban Assault Weapons
Bernie for Immigration Reform
If you ride Big Bend Transportation, please remember to schedule ahead of time.
See you there!

properties.Address:
State Street & West Date Street
San Diego, CA 92101
properties.Description:
Come join us for our Little Italy Farmer's Market Bernie Tabling and Community Canvass. Talk to people and let them know how we all can make a change! It doesn't matter who they are supporting, information gathered and shared is vital!

We will be at State St. and Date St. in Amici Park. Meet us there to find out how to help. Let's use our new online tool (app.berniesanders.com) and populate Bernie's campaign database with as many names as we can!

This is also an opportunity to speak with people regarding Bernie, his policies, and the future with him as our President. Please familiarize yourself with the app before coming out and get signed up on it. It's available on a webpage but also Apple (https://apps.apple.com/us/app/bern-official-bernie-2020-app/id1474294851) and Google Play Stores (https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.berniesanders&hl=en_US).

This is also a great opportunity to wear your Bernie 2020 gear (if you don't have a shirt, support the campaign by ordering here: store.berniesanders.com).

If you are a little on the shy side it is no problem! You can help us man the information table and give out stickers, hand out campaign literature and wave signs. We are looking forward to seeing you and making positive change together!

properties.Title: Board the Bernie Bus and Knock on Doors for the NH Primary!
properties.Description:

properties.Description:
The New Hampshire Primary is upon us! Join us for this Weekend of Action in Weare and Deering as we knock on every single door to ask people to join the political revolution.

Talking to voters face-to-face is the best way to get them out to the polls. Come meet up with our volunteer team and we’ll go knock on doors in Keene to round up votes for Bernie Sanders!

If you’ve never canvassed before, don’t worry! We’ll give you a quick training before you head out.

There are 2 shifts every Saturday: 10 am and 1 pm with a quick 30 minute training before the start of each to make sure you feel confident as you go out to meet voters around town.

After the last canvass shift, we will have a volunteer conversation to thank you for being a part of the political revolution that is going to transform this country into one for the many, not the few!

Just make sure to bring your smartphone, a water bottle and some warm weather gear!

RSVP below if you’ll be there!

properties.Title: Canvassing for Bernie in Nashua, New Hampshire
properties.Description:
Come out and help us knock on every door in NH – Be part of an epic all-day Bernie Sanders canvassing event that will start at 10:00AM in Boston, will stop by Cambridge at 10:30 and will return carpoolers around 7:00 PM.

Talking to voters face-to-face is the best way to get them out to the polls so come meet up with our volunteer team and round up votes for Bernie Sanders! If you’ve never canvassed before, don’t worry! We’ll give you a quick training before you head out.

The Bernie school bus will be leaving from Boston at 10:00 AM from 1155 Tremont St (the Tremont side of Ruggles Station) and will arrive at Alewife in Cambridge at 10:30 AM. It will then be leaving from Alewife at 10:30 AM and head to the Nashua office (77 Derry Rd in Hudson Hudson, NH). Remember without you there is no us – so please join us for all or part of this amazing day of Bernie canvassing!

Please bring warm clothes, a snack, and water. We will provide pizza for lunch!

properties.Title: Holiday Get Bernie on the Ballot - Breakfast Blowout!
properties.Description:
Join fellow Bernie supporters before the "2019 Very Merry Madison Christmas Parade" on Main Street! We’ll have hot coffee, OJ, biscuits & gravy, donuts & fruit available to fuel parade-watchers, beginning at 9:30 am (parade starts at 11 am).

We'll have ballot access petitions for signing & taking home to collect signatures from neighbors, friends, and family to ensure that Bernie is on the ballot. Only ONE month left to collect these signatures!!

We will not be "working the crowd" lining the street, but will inform them of a warm place to step in & learn about our next President over a (free) hot breakfast!

Volunteers & attendees are welcome to hang with us & hit the streets for more signature-gathering after the parade, or do some phone banking during/after the parade.
IMPORTANT: bring your phone & a laptop/tablet/netbook if planning to make calls, and dress according to the weather forecast if petitioning!

properties.Title: Bernie 2020 Barnstorm in Northwood
properties.Description:
Come together with your friends, family, and neighbors to join our historic campaign to defeat Trump and transform America. Bernie understands that when you stand up and fight for working people, when you do not cower to Wall Street and the mega-corporations and billionaires who rigged our economy and our democratic system, when you do this for your whole life, you give people real motivation to vote. Bernie has given us hope. He has changed the narrative and the sense of what is possible in the entire country. He has spent his life on picket lines and in the halls of Congress fighting for working class people.

Now it’s up to all of us to get him into the White House. Join us for our fun barnstorm to meet other volunteers and share why you support Bernie Sanders in this upcoming historic election!

properties.Title: UNLV Rebels for Bernie Countdown to Caucus Party with Senator Nina Turner!
properties.Description:

Please join us at UNLV, where we will dial into a webinar to hear from Senator Turner. During the webinar, we’ll discuss what role you can play on Caucus Day, and how the key to winning is being organized. On Caucus Day, we’ll need volunteers in all of Nevada’s 1,700+ precincts, and having your help will be the thing that puts us over the top.

Please wear an ugly sweater!!! We will make signs and have free food for all.

*This event is for UNLV students.*

properties.Title: ARTS DISTRICT FOR BERNIE! Bernie 2020 Phonebank in Arts District / Downtown LA
properties.Description:
Join us for Bernie in the Arts District, right next to Little Tokyo! Come together with friends, family, and neighbors to call voters in support of Bernie!

Call when you're here: 617.519.3891 OR use the intercom and search for "double J".

properties.Title: Bernie 2020 Phonebank in Escondido, CA
properties.Description:
The Official Bernie Campaign is here in North San Diego!

The CA ‪March 3rd‬ Primary is coming up quick. CA has the most delegates of any state. If you come out to knock and call, we'll win CA, we'll win the Nomination, we'll bring power back to the People in the White House and we'll start fundamentally changing America to work for all of us.
Some of us will be doing Volunteer 2 Volunteer Calls, which are the most powerful calls. All we do is call fellow Bernie Volunteers to plug them into Canvasses, Phone Banks, and other Bernie Events in our area. For every Volunteer you get signed up to Knock or Call, that will become 100s or 1,000s of knocks and calls by the time of the CA Primary ‪on March 3rd.‬ Join the Vol 2 Vol Call Team and let's grow our Bernie community in CD 50!

The rest of us will be using the Bernie Dialer to reach out to Voters to share our stories and get those Votes to WIN! #NotMeUs

PHONEBANKERS: Bring a laptop or tablet (an extra if you have one in case someone needs one), cell phone, phone charger, reusable water bottle, and headphones if you have them. If you can't arrive by ‪5:00 p.m.‬, come when you can. We'll get you set up and started whenever you arrive.

Come together with friends, family, neighbors, the whole local Bernie Community! Phonebanking is one of the most important things you can do. Every call helps us grow our Movement, to turn Bernie supporters out to vote, and to win this election in a People's landslide.

Note: In addition to a cell phone and charger, please bring a laptop or tablet to make Bernie calls, reusable water bottle, and headphones if you have them! #InBernieWeTrust

properties.Title: Tuesday Evening Phonebanking in South Carlsbad for Bernie 2020!
properties.Venue: This event’s address is private. Sign up for more details
properties.Address:
This event’s address is private. Sign up for more details
Carlsbad, CA 92009
properties.Description:
We are only a very few months from the March 2020 CA Primary!

The Official Bernie Campaign is expanding with new Staff to North San Diego and this is our new Congressional District 49 Phone Bank!

There are two options when you join us. Volunteer to Volunteer Call Team phone bank is the first option.

Vol 2 Vol calls are the easiest and most powerful calls you can make. All we're doing is calling fellow Bernie Volunteers to plug them into Canvasses, Phone Banks, and other Bernie Events in our area. Every Volunteer you sign up to Knock or Call, that will become 100s or 1,000s of knocks and calls by the time the newly influential, early CA Primary comes on March 3. Join the Vol 2 Vol Call Team and let's grow our Bernie community in CD 49!

The second phone bank option is the Bernie Dialer.

This is an easy script that we follow and mark the responses of the people we talk to about Bernie. If you want to tell others about why a Bernie Sanders Presidency will help you or those you care about, this is a great opportunity.

You can decide that you want to call other Volunteers (Vol 2 Vol) or that you want to call registered Democrats or No Party Preference voters (Bernie Dialer) when you get here.

PHONE BANKERS: Bring a laptop or tablet (an extra, if you have one, in case someone needs one), cell phone, phone charger, and headphones if you have them. If you can't arrive by 5:00 p.m., come when you can. All your work is valuable! We'll get you set up and started whenever you arrive.

Come together with friends, family, and neighbors to call other volunteers in support of Bernie!

Phonebanking is one of the **most important things** you can do to help our campaign win. Every call helps us grow our movement, to bring out Bernie supporters to vote, and to win this election in a landslide.

Note: In addition to a cell phone, please bring a **laptop or tablet** to use to make Volunteer to Volunteer or the Bernie Dialer calls.

Thank you for signing up! From the 5 freeway, exit Leucadia Boulevard. Go east on Leucadia Boulevard about two miles. Cross El Camino Real. Turn left at the first stoplight east of El Camino Real onto Amargosa Drive. Go up the hill, passing the park on the left. The house is on the left, on the SW corner of the cul-de-sac at Sombrosa Place and Amargosa Drive. See you Tuesday!

• Any questions or suggestions, please reach out to Arturo or Madge Torres at 760.613.7035

properties.Title: The WONDROUS ROTATING Phone Bank of Rural North Iowa!!!
properties.Description: From now until Caucus Day, we will be holding and facilitating phone banks across Northern Iowa (both in centralized locations and remotely). This here is the sign-up for said phone banks!  We will be calling thousands of Iowans across the 4th Congressional District to build the movement to elect our first Democratic Socialist President and to transform our country into one that works for all, not just the few.

properties.Title: Join the Bernie Community Canvass at the College of DuPage in Glen Ellyn, IL
properties.Description:
The youth turnout will be critical for Bernie winning the primary. Come together with friends and fellow students to talk to voters about the election. We'll be asking folks to share what issues are important to them this election, and telling our stories of why we're supporting Bernie in 2020.

You don't have to be a college student to attend! Everyone is welcome to join us engage in the important conversations with voters. We will meet at the table located on the ground floor of the Berg Instructional Center (BIC) building, near the central atrium. It is very close to the police desk and not far from the Starbucks.

The closest parking lots are Fawell B and College 2:
https://www.cod.edu/about/maps_and_directions/pdf/full_campus.pdf

Free Bernie goodies while supplies last!

properties.Title: Central PA for Bernie 2020 Community Canvass in State College
properties.Description: Come together with family, friends and neighbors to talk to voters in your community about the election. We'll be asking folks to share what issues are important to them this election, and telling our stories of why we're supporting Bernie in 2020. Using the BERN app, we will do the critical work of helping the campaign identify who is likely to support Bernie.
